ons/nextcloud-talk/src/monitor.ts:334:  const path = account.config.webhookPath ?? DEFAULT_WEBHOOK_PATH;\nextensions/nextcloud-talk/src/types.ts:49:  webhookPath?: string;\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/SKILL.md:3:description: OpenProse VM skill pack. Activate on any `prose` command, .prose files, or OpenProse mentions; orchestrates multi-agent workflows.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/SKILL.md:26:- Wants to create a reusable workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/SKILL.md:232:- **33-36**: Production workflows (PR auto-fix, content pipeline, feature factory, bug hunter)\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:87:OpenProse provides a declarative syntax for defining multi-agent workflows. Programs consist of statements that are executed sequentially, with each `session` statement spawning a subagent to complete a task.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:342:Use statements import other OpenProse programs from the registry at `p.prose.md`, enabling modular workflows.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:1097:Named blocks create reusable workflow components. Define once, invoke multiple times.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:1221:let workflow = session \"Draft\" -> session \"Edit\" -> session \"Finalize\"\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:1243:block outer-workflow:\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:1251:  do outer-workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:1352:Each parallel branch contains a sequential workflow. The two workflows run concurrently.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:2093:OpenProse provides structured error handling with try/catch/finally blocks, throw statements, and retry mechanisms for resilient workflows.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:2300:Choice blocks allow the OpenProse VM to select from multiple labeled options based on criteria. This is useful for branching workflows where the best path depends on runtime analysis.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:2729:# Execute workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/compiler.md:2824:# Execute workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/02-research-and-summarize.prose:2:# A two-step workflow: research a topic, then summarize findings\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/05-debug-issue.prose:2:# Step-by-step debugging workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/07-refactor.prose:2:# Systematic refactoring workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/08-blog-post.prose:2:# End-to-end content creation workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/13-variables-and-context.prose:6:# Define specialized agents for the workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/14-composition-blocks.prose:38:# Main workflow using blocks\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/15-inline-sequences.prose:20:let workflow = session \"Step 1\" -> session \"Step 2\" -> session \"Step 3\"\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/15-inline-sequences.prose:23:  context: workflow\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/18-mixed-parallel-sequential.prose:16:# Main workflow with mixed composition\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/22-error-handling.prose:2:# Demonstrates try/catch/finally patterns for resilient workflows\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/26-parameterized-blocks.prose:2:# Demonstrates reusable blocks with arguments for DRY workflows\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/27-string-interpolation.prose:61:# Building dynamic workflows\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/27-string-interpolation.prose:62:let workflow_type = session \"What type of document should we create?\"\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/27-string-interpolation.prose:67:Create a {workflow_type} for {audience}.\nextensions/open-prose/skills/prose/examples/28-automated-pr-review.prose:2:# This workflow performs a multi-dimensional review of a codebase changes.\n