ould integrate with hooks/workflow and channel handling, if required by the requested functionality.\n\n### Blocked\n- Prior-memory lookup is unavailable because `memory_search` failed due to an invalid OpenAI API key / embeddings provider error.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use live repo inspection instead of memory-based project history**: Prior-memory lookup was unavailable, so decisions were being made from current code and docs.\n- **Follow existing extension/channel policy patterns**: Search results showed established patterns such as `dmPolicy` / `groupPolicy`, so new work should align with those conventions.\n- **Build on the existing hook system**: The presence of `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests indicates hooks/workflow integration should use the existing internal mechanism.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Trace the exact LINE implementation files and config flow for `webhookPath`, `channelSecret`, `channelAccessToken`, `dmPolicy`, and `groupPolicy`.\n2. Identify the correct inbound message and workflow insertion points using `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests.\n3. Trace VOICEVOX usage paths involving `VOICEVOX`, `audio_query`, and `synthesis`.\n4. Design and implement the requested functionality using the discovered extension and policy patterns.\n5. Validate the implementation against existing tests/patterns and add tests where needed.\n\n## Critical Context\n- No prior history beyond the retained summary.\n- The retained work was in a split turn; the suffix likely continues from repo-discovery results.\n- Search results showed the repo already has:\n  - channel policy patterns in extensions (e.g. IRC onboarding/policy with `dmPolicy` / `groupPolicy`)\n  - a hook system in `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests\n- Important caveat: prior-memory lookup was unavailable, so implementation decisions were being made from live repo inspection only.","firstKeptEntryId":"cb283184","tokensBefore":21007,"details":{"readFi