{"type":"compaction","id":"86e3222a","parentId":"4961da89","timestamp":"2026-03-12T02:12:37.106Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Implement the requested functionality in the `openclaw-control-ui` / `clawdbot-main` repo in a “MILSPEC規格” and software-engineering best-practice style.\n- Identify the exact implementation points for LINE integration, hooks/workflow extension points, and possibly VOICEVOX-related behavior based on existing repo patterns.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User explicitly requested implementation in a “MILSPEC規格” and software-engineering best-practice style.\n- Prior decision/preference lookup via memory was unavailable, so implementation decisions were being made from live repo inspection only.\n- Preserve existing repo conventions and extension patterns rather than inventing new architecture.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Attempted to gather repo-specific guidance by reading `skills/coding-agent/SKILL.md`.\n- [x] Attempted `memory_search` for prior OpenClaw decisions/preferences about LINE, VOICEVOX, and hooks.\n- [x] Identified that `memory_search` failed due to an invalid OpenAI API key / embeddings provider error.\n- [x] Began inspecting the repo to locate implementation points for:\n  - LINE-related config and routing (`webhookPath`, `channelSecret`, `channelAccessToken`, `dmPolicy`, `groupPolicy`)\n  - hooks / workflow / inbound message extension points\n  - VOICEVOX-related code (`VOICEVOX`, `audio_query`, `synthesis`)\n- [x] Ran several `git grep` searches across `docs`, `src`, and `extensions`.\n- [x] Confirmed the repo already contains channel policy patterns in extensions, including IRC onboarding/policy patterns using `dmPolicy` / `groupPolicy`.\n- [x] Confirmed the repo already has a hook system in `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Map the discovered LINE config/routing, hook system, and extension patterns into the requested implementation.\n- [ ] Determine how VOICEVOX-related code should integrate with hooks/workflow and channel handling, if required by the requested functionality.\n\n### Blocked\n- Prior-memory lookup is unavailable because `memory_search` failed due to an invalid OpenAI API key / embeddings provider error.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use live repo inspection instead of memory-based project history**: Prior-memory lookup was unavailable, so decisions were being made from current code and docs.\n- **Follow existing extension/channel policy patterns**: Search results showed established patterns such as `dmPolicy` / `groupPolicy`, so new work should align with those conventions.\n- **Build on the existing hook system**: The presence of `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests indicates hooks/workflow integration should use the existing internal mechanism.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Trace the exact LINE implementation files and config flow for `webhookPath`, `channelSecret`, `channelAccessToken`, `dmPolicy`, and `groupPolicy`.\n2. Identify the correct inbound message and workflow insertion points using `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests.\n3. Trace VOICEVOX usage paths involving `VOICEVOX`, `audio_query`, and `synthesis`.\n4. Design and implement the requested functionality using the discovered extension and policy patterns.\n5. Validate the implementation against existing tests/patterns and add tests where needed.\n\n## Critical Context\n- No prior history beyond the retained summary.\n- The retained work was in a split turn; the suffix likely continues from repo-discovery results.\n- Search results showed the repo already has:\n  - channel policy patterns in extensions (e.g. IRC onboarding/policy with `dmPolicy` / `groupPolicy`)\n  - a hook system in `src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts` and related loader/tests\n- Important caveat: prior-memory lookup was unavailable, so implementation decisions were being made from live repo inspection only.","firstKeptEntryId":"93db47e4","tokensBefore":23714,"details":{"readFi